### Wide Interval: The Octave + Fifth

```scheme
;; A compound interval: C4 to G5 (octave + fifth = 12 + 7 = 19 semitones)
(let ((c4 261.63))
  (audio/play 'tone c4 0.3)
  (audio/play 'tone (* c4 3.0) 0.3))  ;; 3:1 ratio = octave + fifth
```
`<!-- BUILD: runnable standalone; wide melodic leap -->`

**What you hear:** A dramatic leap. Wide intervals sound \"open\" and attention-grabbing.

