### The Tritone

The **tritone** (three whole tones, or six semitones) is the most dissonant interval in Western music. It divides the octave exactly in half.

```scheme
;; A tritone: C4 to F♯4
(audio/play 'tone 261.63 0.3)  ;; C4
(audio/play 'tone 369.99 0.3)  ;; F♯4 (2^(6/12) ≈ 1.414 times C)
```
`<!-- BUILD: runnable standalone; tritone interval -->`

**What you hear:** A tense, unstable interval. It sounds like it *wants* to resolve to something else.

---


### A Chromatic Cluster

```scheme
;; Four adjacent semitones
(audio/play 'tone 261.63 0.2)  ;; C
(audio/play 'tone 277.18 0.2)  ;; C♯
(audio/play 'tone 293.66 0.2)  ;; D
(audio/play 'tone 311.13 0.2)  ;; D♯
```
`<!-- BUILD: runnable standalone; chromatic cluster -->`

**What you hear:** A tight, crunchy sequence. Semitones are the smallest interval in Western tuning, so this sounds \"dense.\"

---


