### A Pentatonic Gesture

The **pentatonic scale** (five notes per octave) is one of the oldest and most universal scale patterns.

```scheme
;; A pentatonic phrase in C: C D E G A
(audio/play 'tone 261.63 0.25)  ;; C
(audio/play 'tone 293.66 0.25)  ;; D
(audio/play 'tone 329.63 0.25)  ;; E
(audio/play 'tone 392.00 0.25)  ;; G
(audio/play 'tone 440.00 0.25)  ;; A
```
`<!-- BUILD: runnable standalone; pentatonic ascending -->`

**What you hear:** A scale with no semitones. It sounds \"open\" and folk-like.

